article.description: — Luke House had 25 points in Drexel's 78-63 victory over UNC Wilmington on Thursday night.
article.headline: House scores 25, Drexel downs UNC Wilmington 78-63
article.linkText: House scores 25, Drexel downs UNC Wilmington 78-63
article.story: PHILADELPHIA -- — Luke House had 25 points in Drexel's 78-63 victory over UNC Wilmington on Thursday night. House was 9 of 12 shooting (5 for 7 from 3-point range) for the Dragons (9-6, 2-0 Coastal Athletic Association). Amari Williams scored 17 points while going 5 of 7 and 7 of 12 from the free throw line, and added six rebounds. Justin Moore shot 4 for 12 (1 for 4 from 3-point range) and 2 of 3 from the free throw line to finish with 11 points. Trazarien White led the Seahawks (9-4, 0-1) in scoring, finishing with 19 points and nine rebounds. Donovan Newby added 16 points for UNC Wilmington. In addition, KJ Jenkins finished with 11 points. These two teams both play Saturday. Drexel visits William & Mary and UNC Wilmington visits Towson. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
